@startuml reverse-hydra
title Reverse Hydra — one contract (head), swappable bodies

skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false
left to right direction

actor "Card terminal\n(gRPC client)" as client

rectangle "Kubernetes — debit-card-api namespace" {
  component "Ingress\ndebit-card-api.local\n**the HEAD: one gRPC contract**" as head
  component "Router Service\nselector: variant = <active>" as router
  component "regular body\nDeployment\nSTIP_Enabled=false" as regular
  component "stip body\nDeployment\nSTIP_Enabled=true" as stip
}

client --> head : gRPC over TLS\n(always the same address)
head --> router
router --> regular : activeVariant = regular
router ..> stip   : activeVariant = stip\n(after a switch)

note bottom of router
  helm upgrade --reuse-values --set activeVariant=stip
  repoints the selector. Both bodies keep running,
  so in-flight calls finish on the old body and the
  client never changes a thing.
end note
@enduml
